00:50:54,502 --> 00:50:55,834
I got a little
carried away.

994
00:50:55,903 --> 00:50:56,835
It was
Christmas Eve
and all.

995
00:50:56,904 --> 00:50:59,705
You put a lot of things
at risk.

996
00:50:59,773 --> 00:51:00,839
We need to get back.

997
00:51:00,908 --> 00:51:01,940
No, not right away.

998
00:51:02,009 --> 00:51:03,241
Yes, right away.

999
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:05,544
No, not right away!

1000
00:51:05,613 --> 00:51:08,013
I need
a little more time.

1001
00:51:08,081 --> 00:51:10,916
I've been dreaming
about this for years.

1002
00:51:10,985 --> 00:51:12,283
I want to be
a human again,

1003
00:51:12,352 --> 00:51:13,585
even if just
for a little while.

1004
00:51:13,654 --> 00:51:15,921
You cannot blame me
for that!

1005
00:51:15,990 --> 00:51:17,890
No, listen,
I'm gonna tackle him,

1006
00:51:17,958 --> 00:51:19,958
take his magic cane,
and we're going back!

1007
00:51:20,027 --> 00:51:23,094
No, it doesn't work
that way!

1008
00:51:23,163 --> 00:51:27,265
The chronometer
is set to our
individual rhythms.

1009
00:51:27,334 --> 00:51:30,903
It's true.
Either we all go back,
or nobody goes back.

1010
00:51:30,971 --> 00:51:34,806
That's right, so you
might want to listen
to my little proposal.

1011
00:51:34,875 --> 00:51:36,174
Now, according
to the clock

1012
00:51:36,243 --> 00:51:37,743
at the Bureau
of Yuletide Affairs,

1013
00:51:37,811 --> 00:51:40,546
we have one hour
and fifteen minutes.

1014
00:51:40,614 --> 00:51:42,981
That's plenty of time.

1015
00:51:43,050 --> 00:51:44,349
I'll make you a deal.

1016
00:51:44,418 --> 00:51:48,954
Give me 60 minutes
to enjoy myself.

1017
00:51:49,023 --> 00:51:50,088
Drink my drink,

1018
00:51:50,157 --> 00:51:51,389
smoke
a few cigarettes,

1019
00:51:51,458 --> 00:51:53,091
maybe dance a little,

1020
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:55,561
and then I'll meet you
back here at midnight.

1021
00:51:55,629 --> 00:51:57,996
- And if we don't?
- Well, if you don't,

1022
00:51:58,065 --> 00:52:00,999
then I'll
pop us through time
like a pinball machine

1023
00:52:01,068 --> 00:52:03,401
until it's too late
for anybody.

1024
00:52:03,470 --> 00:52:04,736
Now, do we have a deal?

1025
00:52:07,307 --> 00:52:09,374
Okay, we have a deal.

1026
00:52:10,878 --> 00:52:12,243
Well, good.

1027
00:52:12,312 --> 00:52:15,280
Then I will see
you kids later.

1028
00:52:15,348 --> 00:52:17,916
Have a good time.

1029
00:52:17,985 --> 00:52:19,517
I know I will.

1030
00:52:22,456 --> 00:52:25,223
Well, I think
I handled that well.

1031
00:52:25,292 --> 00:52:26,424
Yeah, yeah,
especially the end,

1032
00:52:26,493 --> 00:52:28,326
where you let him
walk away from us.

1033
00:52:28,395 --> 00:52:29,360
Good.

1034
00:52:29,429 --> 00:52:32,130
I didn't have a choice.

1035
00:52:32,199 --> 00:52:37,535
So... what are we
gonna do till midnight?

1036
00:52:39,172 --> 00:52:41,006
[coughing]

1037
00:52:41,075 --> 00:52:42,373
Good stuff.

1038
00:52:42,442 --> 00:52:43,942
This is disgusting.

1039
00:52:44,011 --> 00:52:45,110
Yeah, yep.

1040
00:52:45,178 --> 00:52:46,511
And it turns out
in the future

1041
00:52:46,580 --> 00:52:49,715
we find that they're
actually bad for you, too.

1042
00:52:49,783 --> 00:52:51,549
What about this?

1043
00:52:51,619 --> 00:52:54,486
Oh, that's fine,
drink up.

1044
00:52:54,554 --> 00:52:56,888
So you can't
remember anything?

1045
00:52:56,957 --> 00:53:00,959
Well, I mean,
I can remember basic skills
and functions and whatnot.

1046
00:53:01,028 --> 00:53:02,928
You know, I remember
how to tie my shoes,

1047
00:53:02,997 --> 00:53:05,497
and use a computer, and...

1048
00:53:05,565 --> 00:53:08,700
I am surprisingly good
at kung fu. It's just...

1049
00:53:08,769 --> 00:53:12,671
I don't really have a sense
of life in the past.

1050
00:53:12,740 --> 00:53:14,139
Why did they
do that to you?

1051
00:53:14,207 --> 00:53:15,206
I don't know.

1052
00:53:15,275 --> 00:53:16,875
I guess the head office
didn't want

1053
00:53:16,944 --> 00:53:18,877
any one of the Ghosts
having too much power.

1054
00:53:18,946 --> 00:53:21,079
You know, so we can all
only remember the past,

1055
00:53:21,148 --> 00:53:23,381
the present,
or the future.

1056
00:53:23,450 --> 00:53:26,118
Well, the past
is overrated, believe me.

1057
00:53:26,186 --> 00:53:27,519
But you know
the present, right?

1058
00:53:27,587 --> 00:53:29,821
Pretty much, I mean,
the present being today.

1059
00:53:29,890 --> 00:53:31,823
- Mm-hmm.
You know everything?
- Yes.

1060
00:53:31,892 --> 00:53:33,625
I can ask you anything,
and you could answer.

1061
00:53:33,694 --> 00:53:35,060
- Sure.
- Where's Madonna?

1062
00:53:35,129 --> 00:53:36,161
In her bathroom.

1063
00:53:36,229 --> 00:53:37,162
Where's
my wedding ring?

1064
00:53:37,230 --> 00:53:38,263
In the bottom
of your sock drawer.

1065
00:53:38,331 --> 00:53:39,264
Where's my daughter?

1066
00:53:39,332 --> 00:53:40,666
She's making out
with Chip Wattingham

1067
00:53:40,734 --> 00:53:42,167
in the front seat
of his car.

1068
00:53:42,235 --> 00:53:44,069
I'm kidding.
[chuckles]

1069
00:53:44,138 --> 00:53:46,171
She's in the back seat.

1070
00:53:47,808 --> 00:53:49,407
You're pretty funny
for a dead chick.

1071
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:50,942
Yeah? You're pretty handsome.

1072
00:53:51,011 --> 00:53:51,943
What?

1073
00:53:52,012 --> 00:53:54,046
What?

1074
00:53:54,114 --> 00:53:55,513
What'd you say?

1075
00:53:55,582 --> 00:53:57,115
You know,
I think it's getting
kind of busy in here.

1076
00:53:57,184 --> 00:53:58,349
We probably should get going.

1077
00:53:58,418 --> 00:53:59,384
- Really?
- Uh-huh.

1078
00:53:59,452 --> 00:54:00,919
Because of the giant
talking apes?

1079
00:54:00,988 --> 00:54:02,587
Yes, and we don't want you
bumping into yourself.

1080
00:54:02,656 --> 00:54:05,423
If I bump into myself,
that could change
everything and--

1081
00:54:05,492 --> 00:54:07,225
- Exactly.
- What was it you said
a minute ago?

1082
00:54:07,294 --> 00:54:08,660
- I think we should go.
- Really?

1083
00:54:08,729 --> 00:54:10,896
- Yeah.
- All right.

1084
00:54:15,202 --> 00:54:17,435
Hey, thanks a lot!

1085
00:54:17,504 --> 00:54:19,171
Merry Christmas!

1086
00:54:20,607 --> 00:54:22,007
Hey, hey, man!

1087
00:54:22,076 --> 00:54:24,042
What the hell is this?

1088
00:54:24,111 --> 00:54:26,444
[Jack]
All right, okay.

1089
00:54:26,513 --> 00:54:30,215
[Present]
We need a place to hide
until Past comes back.

1090
00:54:30,283 --> 00:54:33,351
We'll find a place. Oh!

1091
00:54:33,420 --> 00:54:34,953
This looks good.
How about here?

1092
00:54:35,022 --> 00:54:37,622
- What?
- Come on in here.

1093
00:54:37,691 --> 00:54:40,759
Hey, buddy!
You were headed for 2...

1094
00:54:40,828 --> 00:54:42,127
- 215?
- Exactly.

1095
00:54:42,196 --> 00:54:45,430
I'm not there anymore.
I'm down here, so hold this.

1096
00:54:45,498 --> 00:54:47,232
Hold this.

1097
00:54:47,300 --> 00:54:49,234
Thank you. Make sure
nobody bothers us, okay?

1098
00:54:49,302 --> 00:54:52,604
- Yeah.
- Enjoy, enjoy.

1099
00:54:54,374 --> 00:54:56,108
What are we doing in here?

1100
00:54:56,176 --> 00:54:58,176
Well, you said to find
a good place to hide,

1101
00:54:58,245 --> 00:55:00,578
and I'd say this is
a great place to hide.

1102
00:55:00,647 --> 00:55:02,781
Oh, no, no, no, no.
No, I don't think so.

1103
00:55:02,850 --> 00:55:05,884
Listen,
we still have time.

1104
00:55:05,953 --> 00:55:08,720
Why should Past
have all the fun?

1105
00:55:16,930 --> 00:55:18,864
Are you okay...

1106
00:55:18,932 --> 00:55:20,132
Present?

1107
00:55:21,835 --> 00:55:24,870
Yes. This is great.

1108
00:55:24,938 --> 00:55:27,438
This was a great idea.

1109
00:55:27,507 --> 00:55:30,108
Thanks.

1110
00:55:30,177 --> 00:55:34,813
You know, I can kind
of understand why Past
wanted to be human again.

1111
00:55:34,882 --> 00:55:37,348
Is he gonna be in trouble
when we go back?

1112
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:39,684
Oh, yeah.

1113
00:55:39,753 --> 00:55:41,719
Are you gonna be
in trouble?

1114
00:55:41,789 --> 00:55:43,354
Oh, yeah.

1115
00:55:43,423 --> 00:55:46,391
Well, I'm not gonna
allow that to happen.

1116
00:55:46,459 --> 00:55:48,894
I'm gonna tell 'em
that you did everything
humanly possible

1117
00:55:48,962 --> 00:55:50,862
to get his little butt
back there,

1118
00:55:50,931 --> 00:55:52,597
and you'll be okay,
trust me.

1119
00:55:59,572 --> 00:56:02,740
You're an interesting guy,
Jack.

1120
00:56:02,810 --> 00:56:04,943
Thanks.

1121
00:56:05,012 --> 00:56:06,577
You are--

1122
00:56:06,646 --> 00:56:08,246
What's the word?

1123
00:56:09,649 --> 00:56:11,016
Perfect.

1124
00:56:13,720 --> 00:56:18,723
So, um, what happened
with your wife?

1125
00:56:18,792 --> 00:56:20,158
She tricked me.

1126
00:56:20,227 --> 00:56:23,728
I thought we had
a happy marriage...

1127
00:56:23,797 --> 00:56:26,364
for almost 20 years.

1128
00:56:26,433 --> 00:56:30,001
And then one day, bam.

1129
00:56:30,070 --> 00:56:33,038
You had no idea?
No warning sign?

1130
00:56:33,106 --> 00:56:34,105
No.

1131
00:56:34,174 --> 00:56:37,775
I mean, we had
the usual disagreements.

1132
00:56:37,845 --> 00:56:41,279
I worked too much.
I didn't spend
enough time with her.

1133
00:56:41,348 --> 00:56:42,714
She'd get really upset.

1134
00:56:42,782 --> 00:56:45,884
But then a few days later,
suddenly she'd get over it.

1135
00:56:45,953 --> 00:56:50,989
Now I know what she was
getting to get over it.

1136
00:56:51,058 --> 00:56:54,692
And the worst part
is the way she did it.

1137
00:56:54,761 --> 00:56:59,030
During my daughter's
Christmas recital.

1138
00:56:59,099 --> 00:57:02,400
She got up,
walked out the door,

1139
00:57:02,469 --> 00:57:04,402
hopped on that dentist,

1140
00:57:04,471 --> 00:57:08,206
and took off
out of our lives.

1141
00:57:08,275 --> 00:57:11,343
He wasn't
even a good dentist.

1142
00:57:11,411 --> 00:57:13,912
I mean, if he had
been an astronaut,
I'd understand,

1143
00:57:13,981 --> 00:57:16,848
but...
it's not right.

1144
00:57:19,019 --> 00:57:21,152
How did your daughter
handle it?

1145
00:57:21,221 --> 00:57:24,055
Well, obviously
better than me.

1146
00:57:24,124 --> 00:57:26,258
She's a strong kid.

1147
00:57:28,996 --> 00:57:33,664
I guess the thing...
that hurts me is

1148
00:57:33,733 --> 00:57:36,768
that I wasted
so many years of my life

1149
00:57:36,836 --> 00:57:40,005
on somebody that
obviously did not love me.

1150
00:57:41,441 --> 00:57:43,641
That's not what it said
in the report.

1151
00:57:43,710 --> 00:57:45,643
What report?

1152
00:57:45,712 --> 00:57:48,280
The one on you.

1153
00:57:48,348 --> 00:57:51,649
According to our records,
you had a better than average
marriage.

1154
00:57:51,718 --> 00:57:55,787
And it produced a daughter
that you love very much.

1155
00:57:55,855 --> 00:58:00,491
So you must've enjoyed those
18 years at least a little bit
while it was happening.

1156
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:02,627
There were moments.

1157
00:58:02,695 --> 00:58:07,999
Maybe she was doing the best
that she could do at the time.

1158
00:58:08,068 --> 00:58:11,569
So why not
let the good memories
outshine the bad memories?

1159
00:58:13,473 --> 00:58:15,373
You don't have
memories, do ya?

1160
00:58:16,676 --> 00:58:19,277
No, and that's what I mean.

1161
00:58:19,346 --> 00:58:22,914
Don't blow it, Jack.

1162
00:58:22,983 --> 00:58:24,882
You know, I thought that
what we did was magic,

1163
00:58:24,952 --> 00:58:29,254
but this-- oh, my gosh--
this is the magic.

1164
00:58:30,590 --> 00:58:33,425
I mean, you still
have a chance.

1165
00:58:33,493 --> 00:58:35,427
Some of us don't.

1166
00:58:37,264 --> 00:58:40,065
Are you unhappy?

1167
00:58:40,133 --> 00:58:45,536
At this moment in time,
I am very happy.

1168
00:58:45,605 --> 00:58:48,974
That makes me
very happy, too.

1169
00:58:54,581 --> 00:58:58,016
To hot tubs
and time travel.

1170
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:09,327
Whoa.

1171
00:59:09,396 --> 00:59:10,395
What?

1172
00:59:10,464 --> 00:59:12,864
I'm having a weird feeling.

1173
00:59:12,932 --> 00:59:15,000
Describe it.

1174
00:59:15,068 --> 00:59:17,835
I don't know.

1175
00:59:17,904 --> 00:59:19,871
I think I have to
go to the bathroom.

1176
00:59:19,939 --> 00:59:22,240
- You think?
- Well, I don't know, Jack.

1177
00:59:22,309 --> 00:59:24,675
I haven't been a human
in a long time.

1178
00:59:24,744 --> 00:59:26,711
You could've fooled me

1179
00:59:26,779 --> 00:59:28,846
'cause you're
really good at it.

1180
00:59:30,017 --> 00:59:31,116
Hold that thought.

1181
00:59:35,122 --> 00:59:37,022
I will.

1182
00:59:38,958 --> 00:59:43,094
♪ Baby, baby, baby, hey ♪

1183
00:59:43,163 --> 00:59:48,233
♪ Ooh, yeah, hey ♪

1184
00:59:48,301 --> 00:59:52,470
♪♪ [disco]

1185
00:59:53,840 --> 00:59:56,541
It's 11:30.
He said he'd be here
by midnight.

1186
00:59:56,609 --> 00:59:57,975
Yeah.

1187
01:00:00,180 --> 01:00:01,212
Jack?

1188
01:00:01,281 --> 01:00:02,647
Okay!

1189
01:00:10,057 --> 01:00:11,423
Come on!

1190
01:00:41,588 --> 01:00:44,722
♪♪ [slow tempo]

1191
01:00:57,003 --> 01:00:58,436
Jack.

1192
01:00:58,505 --> 01:01:00,938
Yeah?

1193
01:01:01,007 --> 01:01:03,040
I'm having
the weirdest feeling.

1194
01:01:03,110 --> 01:01:05,210
You have to tinkle again?

1195
01:01:05,278 --> 01:01:06,644
No.

1196
01:01:06,713 --> 01:01:09,114
Just... I feel, um...

1197
01:01:09,182 --> 01:01:12,783
I don't remember feeling
anything like this.

1198
01:01:12,852 --> 01:01:15,186
It's about you.

1199
01:01:15,255 --> 01:01:19,390
Just... I wish
we had more time.

1200
01:01:19,459 --> 01:01:23,894
Well... there's no time
like the present.

1201
01:01:29,736 --> 01:01:31,669
I thought she
was taking a nap.

1202
01:01:31,738 --> 01:01:33,838
I'll be right back.

1203
01:01:38,845 --> 01:01:42,347
- Hey. How ya doin'?
- Hi.

1204
01:01:43,416 --> 01:01:44,682
Name's Vincent.

1205
01:01:44,751 --> 01:01:45,850
Alison.

1206
01:01:45,918 --> 01:01:48,553
Now, see, that's
a beautiful name.

1207
01:01:48,622 --> 01:01:52,857
A beautiful name
for a beautiful girl.

1208
01:01:52,925 --> 01:01:55,193
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1209
01:01:55,262 --> 01:01:57,162
So, um...

1210
01:01:57,230 --> 01:02:01,466
Are you here
at the lodge alone?

1211
01:02:01,535 --> 01:02:03,301
Yeah, sure am.

1212
01:02:05,972 --> 01:02:08,439
Hey, do you have a room?

1213
01:02:08,508 --> 01:02:09,607
Sure do.

1214
01:02:12,279 --> 01:02:14,345
- Really?
- Yeah, yeah, 433.

1215
01:02:14,414 --> 01:02:15,913
Why don't I go freshen up,

1216
01:02:15,982 --> 01:02:17,848
and I'll meet you there
in 10 minutes.

1217
01:02:17,917 --> 01:02:19,984
Yeah!
[chuckles]

1218
01:02:25,608 --> 01:02:28,276
Um, pardon me.

1219
01:02:30,113 --> 01:02:31,279
[scoffs]

1220
01:02:36,086 --> 01:02:38,219
On our honeymoon.

1221
01:02:54,871 --> 01:02:57,305
Nobody hits on
my future ex-wife!

1222
01:02:57,374 --> 01:03:00,308
Hey! Hey!
Come on, you guys!

1223
01:03:14,891 --> 01:03:19,227
You know, I'm a personal
friend of John Travolta.

1224
01:03:23,199 --> 01:03:24,832
Oh!

1225
01:03:47,623 --> 01:03:48,722
Hey, hey, Curtis.

1226
01:03:48,791 --> 01:03:50,258
Curtis!

1227
01:03:50,326 --> 01:03:52,493
Hey, it's Joey, man,
your roommate Joey.

1228
01:03:52,562 --> 01:03:54,295
Grandmaster Flash?

1229
01:03:54,364 --> 01:03:56,564
Hey, you know that new sound
you was looking for?

1230
01:03:56,632 --> 01:03:59,367
Well, listen to this!

1231
01:04:04,040 --> 01:04:06,840
[groaning]

1232
01:04:08,111 --> 01:04:09,643
- Jack?
- Hey.

1233
01:04:09,712 --> 01:04:10,778
Hey, what's going on?

1234
01:04:10,846 --> 01:04:12,447
Oh, I started a fight.

1235
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:13,881
Pretty stupid, huh?

1236
01:04:13,950 --> 01:04:15,316
No, it was stupid
to leave you on
the dance floor.

1237
01:04:15,385 --> 01:04:18,386
I wanna finish
what we started.

1238
01:04:18,455 --> 01:04:19,820
[growls]

1239
01:04:26,529 --> 01:04:28,929
Get him, honey!

1240
01:04:31,934 --> 01:04:34,168
[screams]

1241
01:04:39,442 --> 01:04:40,674
Well, hello!

1242
01:04:40,743 --> 01:04:41,775
You're here!

1243
01:04:41,844 --> 01:04:43,711
Oh, yeah, but I'm not
too happy about it.

1244
01:04:43,779 --> 01:04:45,446
Take us back!

1245
01:04:45,515 --> 01:04:46,747
Now!

1246
01:04:51,754 --> 01:04:52,720
Jack!

1247
01:04:57,293 --> 01:04:59,227
Thank you, darlin'!
Come on!

1248
01:04:59,295 --> 01:05:00,995
Yes!

1249
01:05:09,806 --> 01:05:13,941
Who are you?

1250
01:05:14,010 --> 01:05:15,509
Ebenezer Scrooge,

1251
01:05:15,578 --> 01:05:17,845
I'm the Ghost
of Christmas Present.

1252
01:05:17,914 --> 01:05:19,747
Boo!

1253
01:05:19,816 --> 01:05:24,018
That is completely
unrealistic.

1254
01:05:24,087 --> 01:05:26,921
Oh, my head.
What happened?

1255
01:05:26,990 --> 01:05:28,555
Um...

1256
01:05:28,625 --> 01:05:32,392
A big guy
hit you really hard.

1257
01:05:32,461 --> 01:05:34,261
Yeah, then what?

1258
01:05:34,330 --> 01:05:36,030
Then you
kicked his butt.

1259
01:05:36,099 --> 01:05:38,966
Oh, I thought so.

1260
01:05:39,035 --> 01:05:41,335
And what are we doing--

1261
01:05:46,743 --> 01:05:49,010
- Just stay here.
- Okay.

1262
01:05:56,986 --> 01:05:59,887
What are you doing?
We have to get back.

1263
01:05:59,956 --> 01:06:01,722
I'm not going back.

1264
01:06:01,791 --> 01:06:03,691
What?

1265
01:06:03,760 --> 01:06:04,892
You heard me.

1266
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:07,628
I am taking control of my life.

1267
01:06:07,697 --> 01:06:10,097
You don't have a life.

1268
01:06:10,166 --> 01:06:12,733
Exactly, because of this job.

1269
01:06:12,802 --> 01:06:14,568
Look, we were handpicked
for our positions.

1270
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:15,970
This is
a worthwhile service.

1271
01:06:16,039 --> 01:06:18,172
You having a good time?

1272
01:06:18,240 --> 01:06:20,107
What does that
have to do with anything?

1273
01:06:20,176 --> 01:06:21,575
Jumping back in time,

1274
01:06:21,644 --> 01:06:24,078
drinking, dancing,

1275
01:06:24,147 --> 01:06:26,413
wanting to smooch.

1276
01:06:26,482 --> 01:06:27,481
So what if I am?

1277
01:06:27,550 --> 01:06:29,616
You, of all people,

1278
01:06:29,686 --> 01:06:33,554
should understand
where I am coming from.

1279
01:06:33,622 --> 01:06:36,290
You're the Ghost
who got the worst deal.

1280
01:06:36,358 --> 01:06:38,926
You can't even remember
the good times!

1281
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:40,928
There is no time
like the present.

1282
01:06:40,997 --> 01:06:44,331
That's because you
haven't been enlightened.

1283
01:06:44,400 --> 01:06:45,866
Go with me?

1284
01:06:45,935 --> 01:06:48,703
Oh, we could go
hopping through time!

1285
01:06:48,771 --> 01:06:51,138
It would be a hoot!

1286
01:06:51,207 --> 01:06:54,608
If we're not back
in a half-an-hour,

1287
01:06:54,677 --> 01:06:57,011
Jack Cameron
will cease to exist.

1288
01:06:57,080 --> 01:06:58,913
Oh!

1289
01:06:58,981 --> 01:07:02,183
Small price to pay
for our happiness.

1290
01:07:02,251 --> 01:07:04,484
Don't you think
we're owed this?

1291
01:07:08,891 --> 01:07:11,558
No!

1292
01:07:11,627 --> 01:07:12,659
Nooo!

1293
01:07:14,496 --> 01:07:16,663
Cruel world!

1294
01:07:16,733 --> 01:07:20,400
You have seen the future,
Ebenezer.

1295
01:07:20,469 --> 01:07:23,237
Oh! That's my daughter!

1296
01:07:23,305 --> 01:07:25,740
[Boy]
How can this be future?

1297
01:07:25,808 --> 01:07:28,375
How can I be dead?

1298
01:07:28,444 --> 01:07:29,910
[Girl]
We all die, Ebenezer.

1299
01:07:29,979 --> 01:07:32,646
It is how we live
that makes us who we are.

1300
01:07:32,715 --> 01:07:35,682
Tonight you have seen your past,
your present, and your future.

1301
01:07:35,752 --> 01:07:39,987
It is now time for you
to realize what your life means.

1302
01:07:40,056 --> 01:07:41,188
I don't understand!

1303
01:07:41,257 --> 01:07:42,857
It is not what
has happened to us

1304
01:07:42,925 --> 01:07:45,893
in the past that makes us
who we are, Scrooge,

1305
01:07:45,962 --> 01:07:48,829
neither is it
this hour's situations
in the present.

1306
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:50,831
It's what's in our hearts.

1307
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:52,233
Our hearts?

1308
01:07:52,301 --> 01:07:54,068
What happens to us
in the past

1309
01:07:54,137 --> 01:07:56,904
should not dictate
to who we are in the future.

1310
01:07:56,973 --> 01:07:58,305
We use our hearts
to go through life

1311
01:07:58,374 --> 01:08:00,274
and play the hand
we're dealt

1312
01:08:00,342 --> 01:08:05,880
to make the most of the time
we have on this earth.

1313
01:08:07,817 --> 01:08:09,316
Yes!

1314
01:08:09,385 --> 01:08:11,819
Yes, it's true!

1315
01:08:11,888 --> 01:08:17,491
I have learned
the true meaning
of Christmas.

1316
01:08:19,361 --> 01:08:23,297
[applause]

1317
01:08:51,327 --> 01:08:52,392
Hey!

1318
01:08:52,461 --> 01:08:54,328
You're gonna miss the end.

1319
01:08:54,396 --> 01:08:55,762
Jack,
what are you doing?
Why did you--

1320
01:08:55,832 --> 01:08:57,965
Why did you
change your clothes?

1321
01:08:58,034 --> 01:09:01,836
Cheating on your husband while
your daughter's on stage
on Christmas Eve?

1322
01:09:01,904 --> 01:09:03,938
Wh-What are you
talking about?

1323
01:09:04,006 --> 01:09:06,073
I'm just going out to the car
to get some lipstick.

1324
01:09:06,142 --> 01:09:07,274
You mean,
like on our honeymoon,

1325
01:09:07,343 --> 01:09:09,977
when you did not go to
the "Deck the Halls" disco

1326
01:09:10,046 --> 01:09:11,979
and did not try
to pick up that guy?

1327
01:09:12,048 --> 01:09:14,281
You knew about that?

1328
01:09:14,350 --> 01:09:16,450
Yeah. I also know you're
on your way to the coat check,

1329
01:09:16,518 --> 01:09:20,921
where you're gonna hook up
with Dr. Roland, DDS.

1330
01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:22,957
What, are you psychic
or something?

1331
01:09:23,025 --> 01:09:25,159
You always were funny,
Alison.

1332
01:09:25,228 --> 01:09:28,996
And I'm gonna miss that
about ya.

1333
01:09:29,065 --> 01:09:32,466
Okay, so now you know.
What do you want from me?

1334
01:09:33,569 --> 01:09:35,169
I want to thank you.

1335
01:09:35,238 --> 01:09:38,605
You want to thank me
for cheating on you.

1336
01:09:38,674 --> 01:09:41,808
No, I want to
thank you for 18 years of
an above-average marriage.

1337
01:09:41,878 --> 01:09:45,112
And I want to thank you
for mothering a wonderful,
beautiful daughter

1338
01:09:45,181 --> 01:09:46,613
who, if all goes well,

1339
01:09:46,682 --> 01:09:49,383
will grow up to be
absolutely nothing like you.

1340
01:09:49,451 --> 01:09:52,719
And I want to thank you
for leaving me right now

1341
01:09:52,788 --> 01:09:54,221
while I still have
a few years left

1342
01:09:54,290 --> 01:09:56,490
to enjoy my life
without you.

1343
01:09:59,795 --> 01:10:00,861
You're welcome.

1344
01:10:00,930 --> 01:10:02,229
Right.

1345
01:10:02,298 --> 01:10:06,901
Well, get her goin'.
The doctor is in.

1346
01:10:10,273 --> 01:10:13,374
That's right.

1347
01:10:13,442 --> 01:10:14,375
Bye.

1348
01:10:17,246 --> 01:10:20,514
I got some bad news for him.
He's lost a loyal customer.

1349
01:10:26,455 --> 01:10:30,524
Tick-tock, time's wasting.

1350
01:10:30,592 --> 01:10:32,359
What's it gonna be?

1351
01:10:32,428 --> 01:10:34,028
No.

1352
01:10:34,096 --> 01:10:36,997
No, I can't do this.

1353
01:10:37,066 --> 01:10:38,832
We need to go home.

1354
01:10:38,901 --> 01:10:40,134
No, no, no, no, no.

1355
01:10:40,202 --> 01:10:43,237
We don't need
to do anything, my dear.

1356
01:10:43,306 --> 01:10:45,439
We're ghosts.

1357
01:10:45,507 --> 01:10:49,176
And if you want this...
[imitates ticking clock]

1358
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:53,347
you're gonna have to take it
out of my cold, dead hands.

1359
01:10:56,319 --> 01:10:57,251
[screams]

1360
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:58,652
[grunting]

1361
01:11:00,689 --> 01:11:03,257
Hey, Pres! You should've
seen me back there!

1362
01:11:03,326 --> 01:11:05,192
- Take us home!
- No, you can't make me!

1363
01:11:05,261 --> 01:11:08,028
- What are you doing?
- Stay out of this, Jack!

1364
01:11:08,097 --> 01:11:10,364
This is between me and him!

1365
01:11:10,433 --> 01:11:14,168
[Past]
Time is almost... up!

1366
01:11:16,172 --> 01:11:19,506
[beeping]

1367
01:11:20,943 --> 01:11:22,977
♪♪ [swing]

1368
01:11:31,887 --> 01:11:34,955
♪ When the Christmas lights
are twinkling ♪

1369
01:11:35,024 --> 01:11:37,824
Cool. We're in
black and white.

1370
01:11:37,893 --> 01:11:39,559
Where are we?

1371
01:11:39,628 --> 01:11:42,496
Hey.

1372
01:11:42,564 --> 01:11:45,499
Those are my parents,
and that's me.

1373
01:11:45,567 --> 01:11:47,567
He tricked me!

1374
01:11:47,636 --> 01:11:49,836
My mom is hot.

1375
01:11:49,905 --> 01:11:53,173
[baby gurgles]

1376
01:11:54,443 --> 01:11:56,477
Nine minutes until
Christmas Day, Jack.

1377
01:11:56,545 --> 01:11:57,577
Let's find him.

1378
01:11:57,646 --> 01:11:58,745
Why?

1379
01:11:58,814 --> 01:12:00,447
What do you mean, why?

1380
01:12:00,516 --> 01:12:02,516
We have to get
out of here!

1381
01:12:02,584 --> 01:12:05,019
It doesn't matter
what time we're stuck in
or what place,

1382
01:12:05,087 --> 01:12:06,720
as long as we're
stuck in it together.

1383
01:12:06,788 --> 01:12:09,456
Oh, that is
the sweetest thing that
anyone has ever said to me,

1384
01:12:09,525 --> 01:12:11,125
but no, I have to do my job!

1385
01:12:11,193 --> 01:12:13,160
We'll get you another job.

1386
01:12:13,229 --> 01:12:15,762
Eight minutes until
Christmas Day, Jack.

1387
01:12:15,831 --> 01:12:16,963
Dance with me.

1388
01:12:17,033 --> 01:12:19,299
Jack, no, we don't
have enough time!

1389
01:12:29,545 --> 01:12:32,179
1958 was
a very good year.

1390
01:12:32,248 --> 01:12:33,313
Ooh.

1391
01:12:33,382 --> 01:12:34,981
I'll say.

1392
01:12:35,051 --> 01:12:36,050
Oh, Jack, no.

1393
01:12:36,118 --> 01:12:37,717
There is something
that I have to tell you.

1394
01:12:37,786 --> 01:12:39,853
I know.
You love me.

1395
01:12:39,922 --> 01:12:40,987
No!

1396
01:12:41,057 --> 01:12:43,190
Uh, I mean--
I mean, yes, probably.

1397
01:12:43,259 --> 01:12:44,724
I love you, too.

1398
01:12:44,793 --> 01:12:45,959
Just listen to me!

1399
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:47,127
This isn't about us.

1400
01:12:47,196 --> 01:12:49,430
This is about you
and what is gonna happen in...

1401
01:12:49,498 --> 01:12:50,697
seven minutes.

1402
01:12:50,766 --> 01:12:52,566
If we don't get you
back in time,

1403
01:12:52,634 --> 01:12:54,901
then all of your Christmases
will no longer be.

1404
01:12:54,970 --> 01:12:56,336
Uh-huh.

1405
01:12:56,405 --> 01:12:59,639
And that means
that old Jack Cameron
will cease to exist.

1406
01:12:59,708 --> 01:13:01,041
So?

1407
01:13:01,110 --> 01:13:02,909
So if you cease to exist,
that means you were
never married!

1408
01:13:02,978 --> 01:13:04,678
My God, that's
good news, honey!

1409
01:13:04,746 --> 01:13:06,513
Jack, that means...

1410
01:13:06,582 --> 01:13:09,083
you never had Suzanne.

1411
01:13:09,151 --> 01:13:11,318
So my daughter...

1412
01:13:11,387 --> 01:13:14,188
Will never be.

1413
01:13:14,256 --> 01:13:16,957
No. You can't do that.
See, that's unacceptable.

1414
01:13:17,025 --> 01:13:19,926
If it's me,
that's one thing,
but not her.

1415
01:13:19,995 --> 01:13:21,361
Believe me,
she's special.

1416
01:13:21,430 --> 01:13:23,730
That kid, I promise you,

1417
01:13:23,799 --> 01:13:25,566
makes the world
a better place
to live in.

1418
01:13:25,634 --> 01:13:27,767
Five minutes, Jack.

1419
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:36,443
You!

1420
01:13:36,512 --> 01:13:37,944
Yes!

1421
01:13:45,053 --> 01:13:47,221
Oh!

1422
01:13:51,093 --> 01:13:53,360
Come back,
you scum little man!

1423
01:13:59,735 --> 01:14:00,700
Whoa!

1424
01:14:00,769 --> 01:14:03,036
Oh! Sorry!

1425
01:14:08,377 --> 01:14:11,011
Why did he have to
break that snowflake?

1426
01:14:25,361 --> 01:14:26,926
[clang]

1427
01:14:26,995 --> 01:14:28,529
Hey!

1428
01:14:33,235 --> 01:14:34,734
Oh.

1429
01:14:35,971 --> 01:14:37,638
Get back over here!

1430
01:14:37,706 --> 01:14:40,240
Okay, here goes.

1431
01:14:40,309 --> 01:14:41,775
Uh!

1432
01:14:41,843 --> 01:14:44,494
Oh!

1433
01:14:44,563 --> 01:14:47,031
Oh, my...

1434
01:14:47,099 --> 01:14:49,733
Ow!

1435
01:14:49,802 --> 01:14:51,601
- That hurt!
- Hey!

1436
01:14:51,670 --> 01:14:53,703
You're not gonna take
my daughter away from me.

1437
01:14:53,772 --> 01:14:56,440
Too late.
It's Christmas Day!

1438
01:14:56,508 --> 01:14:58,208
Not yet, it isn't!

1439
01:15:01,780 --> 01:15:03,513
Jack, 15 seconds.

1440
01:15:04,583 --> 01:15:05,549
So I better go now, huh?

1441
01:15:05,617 --> 01:15:07,117
What? Are you crazy?

1442
01:15:07,186 --> 01:15:09,153
Probably,
but it'll be fine!

1443
01:15:10,389 --> 01:15:11,989
Don't worry!

1444
01:15:14,260 --> 01:15:16,893
Not so fast.

1445
01:15:16,963 --> 01:15:18,996
- Oh!
- Why did you stop me?

1446
01:15:19,065 --> 01:15:21,999
- Future?
- Future?

1447
01:15:22,068 --> 01:15:27,338
You people certainly know
how to create a mess.

1448
01:15:31,944 --> 01:15:33,510
[Jack]
Who's that?

1449
01:15:33,579 --> 01:15:34,778
That's, uh, my boss.

1450
01:15:34,847 --> 01:15:36,613
Oh, hey,
she did a great job.

1451
01:15:36,682 --> 01:15:39,249
That other guy, he's rotten,
but she's pretty great.

1452
01:15:39,318 --> 01:15:41,918
Nice to see you all.

1453
01:15:41,988 --> 01:15:44,754
Past, you have done
the most selfish thing

1454
01:15:44,823 --> 01:15:46,357
anyone has ever done
in the history of time.

1455
01:15:46,425 --> 01:15:47,757
And I checked.

1456
01:15:47,826 --> 01:15:50,361
Yeah, well,
I'm not sorry
for what I did.

1457
01:15:50,429 --> 01:15:52,162
I know, and that's why
you're being replaced.

1458
01:15:52,231 --> 01:15:54,398
Replaced?

1459
01:15:54,467 --> 01:15:55,832
You can't
replace me!

1460
01:15:55,901 --> 01:15:56,933
Why not?

1461
01:15:57,003 --> 01:15:58,702
Because!

1462
01:15:58,770 --> 01:16:01,605
I'm the Ghost
of Christmas Past!

1463
01:16:01,673 --> 01:16:05,976
I've been doing this
for 2,000 years!

1464
01:16:06,045 --> 01:16:09,046
Who could possibly be
qualified to replace me?

1465
01:16:09,115 --> 01:16:13,884
Well, we held a meeting,
and decided on someone
with a strong spirit,

1466
01:16:13,952 --> 01:16:16,387
someone who would appreciate
the past for what it is,

1467
01:16:16,455 --> 01:16:18,055
someone who, in retrospect,

1468
01:16:18,124 --> 01:16:21,725
has been overlooked
and neglected for 2,000 years.

1469
01:16:22,995 --> 01:16:24,495
You.

1470
01:16:25,697 --> 01:16:26,863
Me?

1471
01:16:26,932 --> 01:16:28,399
Her?!

1472
01:16:28,467 --> 01:16:29,466
That's right.

1473
01:16:29,535 --> 01:16:32,036
The head office decided
it would be best.

1474
01:16:32,104 --> 01:16:33,870
You've been deprived
of the past for so long,

1475
01:16:33,939 --> 01:16:37,241
you'll be granted
the knowledge
of all of it.

1476
01:16:37,309 --> 01:16:39,276
Hey!

1477
01:16:39,345 --> 01:16:42,479
What about me?
What am I supposed to do?

1478
01:16:42,548 --> 01:16:45,015
Don't worry.
We have a position
all lined up for you.

1479
01:16:53,375 --> 01:16:58,962
[laughing]

1480
01:16:59,030 --> 01:17:03,600
[screaming]

1481
01:17:03,668 --> 01:17:04,601
Is she okay?

1482
01:17:04,669 --> 01:17:06,103
She'll be fine.

1483
01:17:06,171 --> 01:17:08,438
She was just given
the memories of
all of civilization.

1484
01:17:08,506 --> 01:17:10,506
Give her a moment
to adjust.

1485
01:17:10,575 --> 01:17:14,695
I want my mommy.
I want my mommy!

1486
01:17:14,763 --> 01:17:15,729
[crying]

1487
01:17:15,798 --> 01:17:18,899
Mommy!

1488
01:17:18,967 --> 01:17:23,203
Ahh!

1489
01:17:23,271 --> 01:17:26,406
Ahh.

1490
01:17:26,475 --> 01:17:28,108
So what happens to me?

1491
01:17:28,177 --> 01:17:29,777
It's Christmas.

1492
01:17:29,845 --> 01:17:31,344
You get to go home.

1493
01:17:31,413 --> 01:17:34,548
And I'll take you.

1494
01:17:42,491 --> 01:17:44,491
Whoa, it's here.
It's still here.

1495
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:46,443
Oh.

1496
01:17:46,512 --> 01:17:47,444
What a night, huh?

1497
01:17:47,513 --> 01:17:49,479
It was great.

1498
01:17:49,548 --> 01:17:51,381
And what you said
to your wife

1499
01:17:51,450 --> 01:17:53,483
was pretty good.

1500
01:17:53,552 --> 01:17:55,485
It felt good.

1501
01:17:57,022 --> 01:17:58,821
Oh, Jack, you and I...

1502
01:17:58,890 --> 01:18:01,158
No, you don't have
